main event: An object was sighted at Ellsworth AFB with red, green, and white flashing lights, observed for about 10-20 minutes.
interesting points: Radar contact was made with the object which appeared to orbit., There seemed to be two objects, each the size of a quarter, with approximately 2 miles of separation., The objects exhibited erratic and rapid movements at speeds of 10-20 knots., The sighting was reported to last between 10 to 20 minutes by the observers., One object was initially treated as an aircraft during the investigation.
sighted object: Two objects with flashing lights (red, green, white)
witness description: First Lieutenant Sam W. Moore, experienced intercept controller
